eoman a defender of the rights of americans an eloquent military hero and a master of many guises from rough frontiersman to gentleman philosopher seeking the authentic ethan allen the authors of inventing ethan allen ask how did that ethan allen secure his place in popular culture as they observe this spectacular persona leaves little room for a more accurate assessment of allen as a selfinterested land speculator rebellious mob leader inexperienced militia officer and truthchallenged man who would steer vermont into the british empire drawing extensively from the correspondence in ethan allen and his kin and a wide range of historical political and cultural sources duffy and muller analyze the factors that led to ethan allen’s twohundredyearold status as the most famous figure in vermont’s past placing facts against myths the authors reveal how allen acquired and retained his iconic image how the muchrepeated legends composed after his death coincide with his life why recollections of him are synonymous with the story of vermont and why some vermonters still assign to allen their own cherished and idealized values john j duffy is emeritus professor of english and the humanities vermont state colleges he has been a trustee and executive director of the vermont historical society and editor of its journal vermont history he was chief editor of the vermont encyclopedia  ethan allen and his kin selected correspondence  vols  and early vermont broadsides  he also wrote vermont an illustrated history  and with h nicholas muller iii an anxious democracy aspects of the s  h nicholas muller iii has served as president of colbysawyer college and dean and professor of history at the university of vermont event address  bank street burlingtonus inventing ethan allen paperback by john j duffy h nicholas muller  isbn  availability usually ships in  days published university press of new england  june rd  copyright  phoenix books h n muller iii phd  executive bio compensation hi